WES MOORE, Governor Ch. 163
Chapter 163
(House Bill 972)
AN ACT concerning
Maryland Fair and Agricultural Education Promise Fund – Establishment
(Maryland Fair and Charles J. Otto Agricultural Education Promise Act)
FOR the purpose of establishing the Maryland Fair and Agricultural Education Promise
Fund as a special, nonlapsing fund to provide grants that advance agricultural fairs
and education in the State; requiring interest earnings of the Fund to be credited to
the Fund; requiring a certain amount of proceeds from the State lottery, before being
allocated to the General Fund of the State, to be allocated to the Fund; repealing the
requirement that a certain amount of annual proceeds from the State horse racing
Special Fund be used to promote State agricultural fairs and education; and
generally relating to the Maryland Fair and Agricultural Education Promise Fund.
BY adding to
Article – Agriculture
Section 10–2201 through 10–2203 to be under the new subtitle “Subtitle 22.
Maryland Fair and Agricultural Education Promise Fund”
